<paragraph id="8BBB5906FFECFF8AFEECFBA4FCB0FBAE" blockId="2.[332,878,1016,1067]" box="[332,878,1043,1067]" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">
<heading id="D0F3EE6AFFECFF8AFEECFBA4FCB0FBAE" bold="true" box="[332,878,1043,1067]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFEECFBA4FE39FBAE" bold="true" box="[332,487,1044,1067]" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">Untergattung</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8AFE4EFBA3FCB0FBAE" authority="MULSANT &amp; REY 1874" authorityName="MULSANT &amp; REY" authorityYear="1874" box="[494,878,1043,1067]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xenochara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFE4EFBA3FCB0FBAE" bold="true" box="[494,878,1043,1067]" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFE4EFBA3FDB6FBAE" bold="true" box="[494,616,1043,1067]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">Xenochara</emphasis>
MULSANT &amp; REY 1874
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB5906FFECFF8AFF37FBFFFDE2FB38" blockId="2.[151,1059,1103,1213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">
Die Arten der 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8AFE92FBE0FE58FBE1" authorityName="LIKOWSKY, Aedoeagus" authorityYear="1982" box="[306,390,1103,1125]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heeri">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFE92FBE0FE58FBE1" box="[306,390,1103,1125]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">A. heeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-Gruppe [Untergattung 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8AFDDBFBFFFC37FBE0" authority="MULSANT &amp; REY 1874" authorityName="MULSANT &amp; REY" authorityYear="1874" box="[635,1001,1103,1125]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xenochara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFDDBFBFFFD34FBE1" box="[635,746,1103,1124]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">Xenochara</emphasis>
MULSANT &amp; REY 1874
</taxonomicName>
] sind durch die Kombination folgender Merkmale charakterisiert: Körper schwarz, Halsschild breit und dicht punktiert, Flügeldecken am Hinterrand deutlich ausgebuchtet. Querfurchen der vorderen Tergite grob punktiert.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31E0A8DFFECFF8BFF37FB7CFD21FEC4" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="374" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBB5906FFECFF8AFF37FB7CFDC1FA6F" blockId="2.[151,1059,1228,1514]" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">
Die Vertreter der 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8AFEEEFB7DFE7EFB67" authorityName="LIKOWSKY, Aedoeagus" authorityYear="1982" box="[334,416,1229,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heeri">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFEEEFB7DFE7EFB67" box="[334,416,1229,1250]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">A. heeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-Gruppe besitzen einen grundsätzlich ähnlichen Bau der paarigen Sklerite im Aedoeagus; diese enden dorn-, haken- oder fischmaulartig. Bei den Arten 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8AFF37FAB7FEE0FA99" authorityName="LOHSE" authorityYear="1988" box="[151,318,1287,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucharoensis">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFF37FAB7FEE0FA99" box="[151,318,1287,1308]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">A. bucharoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8AFEEEFAB7FE63FA99" authorityName="ROUBAL, Westkaukasus, Adygeja" authorityYear="1968" box="[334,445,1287,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="honesta">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFEEEFAB7FE63FA99" box="[334,445,1287,1308]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">A. honesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8AFE57FAB7FDACFA99" authorityName="LIKOWSKY, Allgau, Grunten" authorityYear="1982" box="[503,626,1287,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvetica">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFE57FAB7FDACFA99" box="[503,626,1287,1308]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">A. helvetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ist der Medianlobus im vorderen Drittel abgebogen und dort verschieden stark, bei 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8AFDF2FA95FD15FABC" authorityName="LIKOWSKY, Allgau, Grunten" authorityYear="1982" box="[594,715,1316,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvetica">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFDF2FA95FD15FABC" box="[594,715,1316,1338]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">A. helvetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fast blattartig, verbreitert. Bei 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8AFBACFA95FF38FAD2" authorityName="ROUBAL, Westkaukasus, Adygeja" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="honesta">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFBACFA95FF38FAD2" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">A. honesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8AFE81FAF2FE43FAD2" authorityName="LIKOWSKY, Allgau, Grunten" authorityYear="1982" box="[289,413,1346,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvetica">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFE81FAF2FE43FAD2" box="[289,413,1346,1367]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">A. helvetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sind die letzten beiden Sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="133F4583FFECFF8AFC91FAF1FC54FAD2" box="[817,906,1345,1367]" captionStart="Abb" captionStartId="27.[151,194,1202,1222]" captionTargetBox="[212,949,231,1156]" captionTargetId="figure-27@27.[192,971,428,811]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Abb. 55-56: Aleochara helvetica LIKOWSKÝ, Allgäu, Grünten: (55) Sternit VII; (56) Sternit VIII; Massstab: 0,2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5409073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5409073/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">Abb. 55</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133F4583FFECFF8AFC39FAF1FC6DFAD2" box="[921,947,1345,1367]" captionStart="Abb" captionStartId="28.[151,194,1319,1339]" captionTargetBox="[182,950,224,1289]" captionTargetId="figure-42@28.[151,983,677,994]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Abb. 57-59: Aleochara honesta ROUBAL: (57) Aedoeagus, Lateralansicht, Kaukasus, Krasnaja Polnaja; (58) Sternit VII; (59) Sternit VIII; Massstab: Abb. 57: 0,5 mm, Abb. 58, 59: 0,2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5409075" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5409075/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">58</figureCitation>
) und VIII (
<figureCitation id="133F4583FFECFF8AFF3FFAEFFF28FAF0" box="[159,246,1375,1397]" captionStart="Abb" captionStartId="27.[151,194,1202,1222]" captionTargetBox="[212,949,231,1156]" captionTargetId="figure-27@27.[192,971,428,811]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Abb. 55-56: Aleochara helvetica LIKOWSKÝ, Allgäu, Grünten: (55) Sternit VII; (56) Sternit VIII; Massstab: 0,2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5409073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5409073/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">Abb. 56</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133F4583FFECFF8AFEA2FAEFFEC2FAF0" box="[258,284,1375,1397]" captionStart="Abb" captionStartId="28.[151,194,1319,1339]" captionTargetBox="[182,950,224,1289]" captionTargetId="figure-42@28.[151,983,677,994]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Abb. 57-59: Aleochara honesta ROUBAL: (57) Aedoeagus, Lateralansicht, Kaukasus, Krasnaja Polnaja; (58) Sternit VII; (59) Sternit VIII; Massstab: Abb. 57: 0,5 mm, Abb. 58, 59: 0,2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5409075" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5409075/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">59</figureCitation>
) der durch dichte Borstensäume und Haarborstenfelder ausgezeichnet; die bei den anderen Arten fehlen. Dieses Merkmal tritt sonst bei keiner der paläarktischen Arten der Untergattung 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8AFD87FA2AFD48FA2A" authorityName="MULSANT &amp; REY" authorityYear="1874" box="[551,662,1434,1455]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xenochara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFD87FA2AFD48FA2A" box="[551,662,1434,1455]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">Xenochara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auf, und hat wahrscheinlich konstituiven Charakter. Das Flagellum aller Arten der 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8AFD2AFA07FD01FA49" authorityName="LIKOWSKY, Aedoeagus" authorityYear="1982" box="[650,735,1463,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heeri">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8AFD2AFA07FD01FA49" box="[650,735,1463,1484]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">A. heeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-Gruppe ist ziemlich kurz und kaum halb so lang wie der Aedoeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB5906FFECFF8BFF37FA49FD21FEC4" blockId="2.[151,1059,1529,1580]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1059,211,321]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="374" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">
Aufgrund äusserer Ähnlichkeiten (Punktierung der Tergite, Flügeldeckenhinterrand) und den Innenstrukturen des Aedoeagus sind die nächsten Verwandten in der Gruppe um 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFECFF8BFBACF9A7FE08FF6D" authority="ST. CLAIRE DEVILLE" authorityName="ST. CLAIRE DEVILLE" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="374" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmotae">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFECFF8BFBACF9A7FF23FF6C" italics="true" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="374" pageId="2" pageNumber="373">A. marmotae</emphasis>
ST. CLAIRE DEVILLE
</taxonomicName>
zu finden. Die 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFEDFF8BFDD5FF64FD27FF6C" box="[629,761,212,233]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmotae">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFEDFF8BFDD5FF64FD27FF6C" box="[629,761,212,233]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="374">A. marmotae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-Arten besitzen eine ähnliche Genitalmorphologie und besiedeln dieselben alpinen- und hochalpinen Lebensräume. Eine Abklärung der Verwandtschaftsverhältnisse wird erst durch eine phylogenetische Revision aller 
<taxonomicName id="4C042285FFEDFF8BFE8BFE9BFE44FEC5" authorityName="MULSANT &amp; REY" authorityYear="1874" box="[299,410,299,320]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xenochara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9708514FFEDFF8BFE8BFE9BFE44FEC5" box="[299,410,299,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="374">Xenochara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-Gruppen und -Arten möglich sein.
</paragraph>
